{"title": "Article 2346", "body": {"ops": [{"insert": "Digital stabilization of unstable equilibria of linear systems may lead to small amplitude stochastic-like oscillations. We show that these vibrations can be related to a deterministic chaotic dynamics induced by sampling and quantization. A detailed analytical proof of chaos is presented for the case of a PD controlled oscillator: it is shown that there exists a finite attracting domain in the phase-space, the largest Lyapunov exponent is positive and the existence of a Smale horseshoe is also pointed out. The corresponding two-dimensional micro-chaos map is a multi-baker map, i.e. it consists of a finite series of baker's maps.\n"}]}, "text": "Digital stabilization of unstable equilibria of linear systems may lead to small amplitude stochastic-like oscillations. We show that these vibrations can be related to a deterministic chaotic dynamics induced by sampling and quantization. A detailed analytical proof of chaos is presented for the case of a PD controlled oscillator: it is shown that there exists a finite attracting domain in the phase-space, the largest Lyapunov exponent is positive and the existence of a Smale horseshoe is also pointed out. The corresponding two-dimensional micro-chaos map is a multi-baker map, i.e. it consists of a finite series of baker's maps.\n", "updatedAt": 1714680235, "embeddings": ["0.506396", "-0.08757697", "1.1396887", "0.27592656", "0.17636539", "0.023596674", "0.3365404", "0.9349072", "0.14692605", "-0.1411667", "0.10461436", "0.67939323", "-0.463433", "0.20513953", "0.026674971", "0.17021587", "0.10804473", "0.17211558", "0.19955258", "0.8478237", "-0.26243746", "-0.12705562", "0.37766004", "-0.9784329", "-0.2007081", "0.391634", "-0.8026664", "0.568525", "-0.53478533", "0.09842901", "0.12903532", "-0.2646144", "-0.6640548", "0.5068868", "-0.8580622", "-0.45835096", "0.47831354", "-0.9678034", "-1.2028102", "-0.6316385", "0.08527579", "-0.8666773", "0.0042930106", "0.0634355